# UI Patterns

## Component Structure

- **Server components** (default): Pages in `src/app/`, fetch data via D1 directly
- **Client components** (`"use client"`): Interactive pieces in `src/components/`, use `fetch()` to API routes
- Keep client components small and focused; pass data from server parents

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS v4 with custom theme variables defined in `src/app/globals.css`
- Use semantic classes: `bg-surface`, `bg-surface-alt`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`
- Dark mode: use `dark:` prefix. Avoid hardcoded colors — use CSS variables
- Cards: `bg-surface-alt rounded-xl border border-border p-4`
- Ensure color contrast in both light and dark modes

## Common Patterns

```tsx
// Client component with API call
"use client";
import { useState } from "react";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";

export function MyComponent({ data }) {
  const router = useRouter();
  const [saving, setSaving] = useState(false);

  async function handleAction() {
    setSaving(true);
    const res = await fetch("/api/...", { method: "POST", ... });
    if (res.ok) router.refresh(); // revalidate server data
    setSaving(false);
  }
}
```

## Mobile-First

The app is primarily used on phones. Ensure all interactions work on touch:
- Buttons need adequate tap targets (min 44px)
- No drag-and-drop (conflicts with scroll) — use tap-to-select patterns
- Test layouts at 375px width
